   182	
   183	## File-by-file design
   184	
   185	### `reference/compose/compose.yaml`
   186	
   187	Three services and three named volumes. `postgres` and `gitea`
   188	mount their own data volumes; `blob-init` is a one-shot service
   189	whose only purpose is to ensure `eden-blob-data` is created.
   190	
   191	```yaml
   192	name: eden-reference
   193	
   194	services:
   195	  postgres:
   196	    image: postgres:16.6-alpine
   197	    container_name: eden-postgres
   198	    restart: unless-stopped
   199	    environment:
   200	      POSTGRES_DB: ${POSTGRES_DB:-eden}
   201	      POSTGRES_USER: ${POSTGRES_USER:-eden}
   202	      POSTGRES_PASSWORD: ${POSTGRES_PASSWORD:?POSTGRES_PASSWORD must be set}
   203	    ports:
   204	      - "${POSTGRES_HOST_PORT:-5433}:5432"
   205	    volumes:
   206	      - eden-postgres-data:/var/lib/postgresql/data
   207	    healthcheck:
   208	      test: ["CMD-SHELL", "pg_isready -U ${POSTGRES_USER:-eden} -d ${POSTGRES_DB:-eden}"]
   209	      interval: 5s
   210	      timeout: 3s
   211	      retries: 10
   212	      start_period: 10s
   213	
   214	  gitea:
   215	    image: gitea/gitea:1.22.6-rootless
   216	    container_name: eden-gitea
   217	    restart: unless-stopped
   218	    environment:
   219	      GITEA__server__DOMAIN: localhost
   220	      GITEA__server__ROOT_URL: http://localhost:${GITEA_HOST_PORT:-3001}/
   221	      GITEA__server__HTTP_PORT: "3000"
   222	      # SSH_PORT is the *advertised* port (shown in clone URLs); it must
   223	      # match the host-side mapping so SSH clones work. SSH_LISTEN_PORT
   224	      # is what Gitea binds inside the container, kept fixed at 2222
   225	      # so the published mapping below stays valid even when a user
   226	      # overrides GITEA_SSH_HOST_PORT to dodge a host collision.
   227	      GITEA__server__SSH_PORT: "${GITEA_SSH_HOST_PORT:-2222}"
   228	      GITEA__server__SSH_LISTEN_PORT: "2222"
   229	      GITEA__database__DB_TYPE: sqlite3
   230	      GITEA__database__PATH: /var/lib/gitea/data/gitea.db
   231	      GITEA__security__INSTALL_LOCK: "true"
   232	      GITEA__security__SECRET_KEY: ${GITEA_SECRET_KEY:?GITEA_SECRET_KEY must be set}
   233	      GITEA__security__INTERNAL_TOKEN: ${GITEA_INTERNAL_TOKEN:?GITEA_INTERNAL_TOKEN must be set}
   234	      GITEA__service__DISABLE_REGISTRATION: "true"
   235	      GITEA__metrics__ENABLED: "false"
   236	      GITEA__log__LEVEL: Warn
   237	    ports:
   238	      - "${GITEA_HOST_PORT:-3001}:3000"
   239	      - "${GITEA_SSH_HOST_PORT:-2222}:2222"
   240	    volumes:
   241	      - eden-gitea-data:/var/lib/gitea
   242	    healthcheck:
   243	      test: ["CMD", "wget", "-q", "--spider", "http://localhost:3000/api/v1/version"]
   244	      interval: 5s
   245	      timeout: 3s
   246	      retries: 20
   247	      start_period: 30s
   248	
   249	  blob-init:
   250	    # One-shot service whose only job is to ensure eden-blob-data
   251	    # exists at compose-up time. Compose does NOT create an unmounted
   252	    # top-level volume — that was verified during planning by a quick
   253	    # spike — so without this service the volume would not exist
   254	    # until 10b/10d's first real mounter ran. 10a's contract is
   255	    # "volume exists" only; ownership/perms are 10d's responsibility.
   256	    image: busybox:1.36.1
   257	    container_name: eden-blob-init
   258	    restart: "no"
   259	    # Deliberately no chmod/chown: 10a's contract is "volume exists,"
   260	    # not "writable by the eventual 10d producer." Ownership belongs
   261	    # to whichever uid/gid 10d picks for its blob-writing service.
   262	    command: ["sh", "-c", "mkdir -p /var/lib/eden/blobs && echo blob-volume ready"]
   263	    volumes:
   264	      - eden-blob-data:/var/lib/eden/blobs
   265	
   266	volumes:
   267	  eden-postgres-data:
   268	  eden-gitea-data:
   269	  eden-blob-data:
   270	```
   271	
   272	Notes on shape choices:
   273	
   274	- `name: eden-reference` is the project name. `compose up`,
   275	  `compose down`, and `compose ps` use this; without it the project
   276	  defaults to the directory name (`compose`) which is uselessly
   277	  generic.
   278	- `${VAR:?msg}` syntax for required secrets means `compose up`
   279	  fails fast with a clear message if the user hasn't copied
   280	  `.env.example` to `.env`. `${VAR:-default}` for optional values.
   281	- Port collisions on the host are likely (a developer probably has
   282	  Postgres 5432 in use; some have Gitea 3000). Defaulting host-side
   283	  to 5433 / 3001 / 2222 sidesteps the most common collisions.
   284	- `GITEA__security__INSTALL_LOCK: "true"` — skip the first-run
   285	  installer wizard. With `INSTALL_LOCK=true` plus
   286	  `DISABLE_REGISTRATION=true`, Gitea boots straight into headless
   287	  mode. Admin user creation happens in 10c.
   288	- The blob volume is declared at the top level and mounted by the
   289	  one-shot `blob-init` service so Compose actually creates it at
   290	  `compose up` (an unmounted declaration alone does not, per the
   291	  empirical spike noted in Core Design Decisions). Downstream
   292	  services in 10b/10d mount the same volume at `/var/lib/eden/blobs`.
   293	  `--wait` exits 0 when `blob-init` exits 0; the smoke test re-checks
   294	  via `docker volume inspect`.
   295	- No `networks:` block: services land on Compose's default
   296	  bridge network. Service discovery via container name
   297	  (`postgres:5432`, `gitea:3000`) just works; explicit network
   298	  declarations matter for multi-stack overlap, which 10a doesn't
   299	  have.
   300	
   301	### `reference/compose/.env.example`
   302	
   303	Plain dotenv. Comments document each value. Ships dev-only secrets:
   304	
   305	```dotenv
   306	# EDEN reference Compose stack — example environment.
   307	# Copy to ".env" for local use; "compose up" reads from .env automatically.
   308	# CI uses these defaults verbatim; do NOT use these in production.
   309	
   310	# --- Postgres ---
   311	POSTGRES_DB=eden
   312	POSTGRES_USER=eden
   313	POSTGRES_PASSWORD=eden-dev-password-change-me
   314	POSTGRES_HOST_PORT=5433
   315	
   316	# --- Gitea ---
   317	# SECRET_KEY: gitea uses this for cookie / CSRF / 2FA encryption.
   318	# Generate with: gitea generate secret SECRET_KEY  (or 64 hex chars).
   319	GITEA_SECRET_KEY=0123456789abcdef0123456789abcdef0123456789abcdef0123456789abcd
   320	# INTERNAL_TOKEN: gitea uses this for inter-component auth.

